node.text: Join Julien’s Auctions on Friday, November 30th and Saturday, December 1st in Los Angeles and live online at Julien's Live for our "Property From The Collection of Hugh M. Hefner Foundation in support of organizations that advocate for and defend civil rights, with special emphasis on First Amendment rights and rational sex and drug policies since 1964.

node.text: Visiting the tomb of Rameses. There are multiple tombs of kings from different generations here which is why the area is referred to as “The Valley of the Kings.” Egypt is such a surreal place and I’m always blown away and feel drawn to something higher than myself when exploring the culture and practices of different countries, especially these ancient ones in Egypt. Thank you @nourelnil for setting us up with the perfect tour guide for this magical adventure xoxo

node.text:
I’m so happy to be nearing my collaboration with @unitedplanet as a cultural ambassador to Mexico and being able invite you along with us. ⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
Travel dates: October 27-November 3⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
Join the experience where you’ll:⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
❤️ Discover authentic Mexican culture ⁣⁣⁣
❤️ Experience Dia De Los Muertos⁣⁣⁣
❤️ Go on nature hikes to waterfalls ⁣⁣⁣
❤️ Relax in outdoor Mexican steam baths ⁣⁣⁣
❤️ Build relationships w/ the local community ⁣⁣⁣
❤️ Make a positive difference through volunteering & supporting local and indigenous businesses and non profits ⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
Together we will build cross cultural relationships, discover rich traditions and nature, and empower communities. ⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
Limited to 12 people. Link in bio.

node.text: Brb moving to Mexico ;) I just love the jungle vibes so near the ocean. The way the sun hits, and how the whole entire feeling is just like a warm hug from nature. It’s a place that sparks the emotions for sure. Te amo México. 🌊 🌱 🌅
